<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9241] SASL Clients are not forced to re-authenticate if they don&apos;t leverage SaslAuthenticateRequest</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9241</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Brokers are supposed to force SASL clients to re-authenticate (and kill such connections in the absence of a timely and successful re-authentication) when SASL Re-Authentication &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-368%3A+Allow+SASL+Connections+to+Periodically+Re-Authenticate&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;(KIP-368)&lt;/a&gt;  is enabled via a positive `connections.max.reauth.ms` configuration value.  There is a flaw in the logic that causes connections to not be killed in the absence of a timely and successful re-authentication &lt;em&gt;if the client does not leverage the SaslAuthenticateRequest API&lt;/em&gt; (which was defined in &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-152+-+Improve+diagnostics+for+SASL+authentication+failures&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;KIP-152&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
